itemLabel: Frederick Fiennes, 16th Baron Saye and Sele

wikipedia_page.main: The Venerable Frederick Fiennes, 16th Baron Saye and Sele,  MA (1799–1887) was Archdeacon of Hereford from 1863 to 1887.

response: * Frederick Benjamin Twisleton (1799–1887), also Frederick Fiennes, 16th Baron Saye and Sele, son of Thomas Twisleton

Fiennes was born on 14 April 1911, the son of Gerald Yorke Twisleton-Wykeham-Fiennes and his wife Gwendolen, née Gisborne; part of the Twisleton-Wykeham-Fiennes family, on his father's side he was the great-grandson of Frederick Fiennes, 16th Baron Saye and Sele.Burke's Peerage (2003), vol. 3, pp. 3533–3534. Educated as "Founders' kin" at Winchester College (he was descended from William of Wykeham), Fiennes went up to Balliol College, Oxford, where he read classics; graduating in 1934 with a first-class degree, he won several named scholarships and the Gaisford Prize."Sir John Fiennes", The Times (London), 23 April 1996, p. 21.
